        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 31 at 1:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 145 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles northwest of Waynesville, or near Maggie Valley, moving east at
40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Candler, Lake Junaluska, Leicester, Waynesville, Maggie Valley, Cove
Creek, Clyde, West Asheville, Canto, and Balsam.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
